'  pOptions.showSidebar          = false;',
'  pOptions.showRuler            = true;',
'  pOptions.hideMenu             = false;',
'  pOptions.classicMenu          = false;',
'  pOptions.logPrefixAsStaticId  = true;',
'  pOptions.height               = "70vh";',
'  pOptions.zoomLevel            = 8;',
'  pOptions.darkMode             = false;',
'  pOptions.hidePoweredBy        = false;    ',
'                  ',
'  return pOptions;',
'}'))
,p_depending_on_has_to_exist=>true
,p_help_text=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<p>',
'  The attribute value must be anonymous function accepting only one parameter which is JSON object containing all plug-in options rendered from the plug-in package on page load.',
'  The function must return this JSON object in order to initialize the plug-in.',
'</p>',
'',
'See the example function below',
'',
'<pre>function( pOptions ) {',
'  return pOptions;',
'}</pre>',
'',
'The supported JSON properties are listed below:',
'<dl>',
'  <dt>logPrefixAsStaticId</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag detemining whether the plug-in widget produce JavaScript logs (in application debug mode) using region static ID as the prefix or is using the default prefix.',
'    Enabling this property is helpful when debugging multiple instances of the plug-in on same page.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>height</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    The given CSS height value is applied to the plug-in region. ',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>zoomLevel</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    An <code>Number</code> from <code>1</code> to <code>20</code>. ',
'    Each zoom level maps to a different initial zoom in percentage. ',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>hidePoweredBy</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the AOE logo is displayed in the new file panel.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>darkMode</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the editor theme is dark or light.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>flushUiPreferences</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the end-user UI preferences are flushed before loading the editor.',
'',
'    Flushing end-user''s preferences is required to enforce the editor UI using showStatusBar, showSideBar and showRuler.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>showStatusBar</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the editor''s status bar is visible.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>showSidebar</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the editor''s sidebar is visible.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>showRuler</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the editor''s ruler is visible.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>classicMenu</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the editor menu layout is tabbed or classic.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>hideMenu</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <code>Boolean</code> flag determining whether the document editor menu is displayed.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>checkEditorTimeout</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    A number of <code>Milliseconds</code> defining delay starting first countdown defined via <code>checkEditorCountdowns</code> property.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>checkEditorCountdowns</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <p>',
'      An <code>Array</code> of <code>Seconds</code> defininig countdowns starting values.',
'      When a countdown ends, the plug-in reloads the AOE editor iframe starting a new request loading a document.',
'      Every array entry is separate countdown. ',
'      The entries number defines how many countdowns have to finish before the plug-in gives up and raise an error on initializing the AOE editor.',
'    </p>',
'    <p>These countdowns are meant to reinitialize the plug-in request loading a document when the AOE server iframe is not loaded when requested.</p>',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>checkDocTimeout</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'  A number of <code>Milliseconds</code> defining delay starting countdown defined via <code>checkDocCountdown</code> property.',
'  </dd>',
'',
'  <dt>checkDocCountdown</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    <p>',
'      Number of <code>Seconds</code> definining countdown starting value before the plug-in gives up and raise an error on loading document.',
'    </p>',
'    <p>',
'      This countdown is meant to inform the end-user that the AOE server failed to load a document after its iframe is loaded.',
'    </p>',
'  </dd>',
'',
'</dl>'))
,p_attribute_comment=>wwv_flow_string.join(wwv_flow_t_varchar2(
'<dt>menuHideItems</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'    An <code>Array</code> of menu entries IDs. ',
'    The menu customization is supported only when <strong>classicMenu</strong> is set to <strong>true</strong>.',
'    Please read the plug-in documentation for the full list of menu entries that can be hidden.',
'    ',
'  </dd>',
'',
'',
'<dt>buttons</dt>',
'<dd>',
'  An <code>Array</code> of JSON objects defining custom buttons to be added to the AOE toolbar.',
'  Clicking a custom button triggers <strong>AOE Button Clicked</strong> event. ',
'  Learn more about custom button JSON structure in the section <strong>Examples</strong> below.<br><br>',
'  <i>The possibility to add custom buttons is experimental and might be removed or updated.</i>',
