'',
'<p>',
'  Please read the full plug-in documentation at http://www.apexofficeedit.com for more information.',
'</p>',
'',
'<dl>',
'  <dt>Custom button</dt>',
'  <dd>',
'',
'    A custom button JSON must implement the following properties:',
'    <dl>',
'      <dt>id</dt>',
'      <dd>',
'        A unique button ID is used to identify clicked custom buttons when the plug-in event <strong>AOE Button Clicked</strong> is triggered. ',
'      </dd>',
'      <dt>imgurl</dt>',
'      <dd>',
'        An URL to the button SVG icon. ',
'        <i>To reference <strong>APEX Office Print</strong> icon use <code>#PLUGIN_PREFIX#aop.svg</code>.</i>',
'      </dd>',
'      <dt>label</dt>',
'      <dd>',
'        A text to be displayed when custom button is hovered.',
'      </dd>',
'      <dt>insertBefore</dt>',
'      <dd>',
'        An existing button ID before which a custom button is added. ',
'        For example: <code>save</code>, <code>print</code>.',
'',
'        Placing custom button before existing button works only when <strong>Menu Layout</strong> is set to <strong>Classic</strong>.',
'        Otherwise, the custom button is added in the toolbar before menu entries.',
'        See documentation for supported values.',
'        ',
'      </dd>',
'    </dl>',
'',
'  </dd>',
'</dl>'))
);
